    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-01-08T10:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-01-08T10:35:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <head>185. Memorandum of Conversation Between President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        type="from">Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1" type="to">Dulles</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d185fn0">Source: Eisenhower Library, Dulles
                        Papers, Meetings with the President. Confidential; Personal and
                        Private.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1959-01-08T10:35:00">January 8, 1959, 10:35 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of an unrelated matter.]</p>
                <p>2. I discussed with the President the attitude of General <persName
                        corresp="#p_DGC1">De Gaulle</persName> toward <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> and our problems. I referred particularly to the memorandum of
                    conversation between General <persName corresp="#p_DGC1">De Gaulle</persName>
                    and <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Selwyn Lloyd</persName> which indicated
                    resentment that France was in effect under United States control through <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> whereas U.S. military power was entirely
                        independent.<note n="1" xml:id="d185fn1">See <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p2#d83">Part 2, Document 83</ref>.</note> I
                    mentioned the tripartite talks which we had planned and my hope that this might
                    alleviate the situation.<note n="2" xml:id="d185fn2">See <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p2#d77">Part 2, Documents 77</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v07p2#d78">78</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of unrelated matters.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">JFD</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
